ly-complete-histo-1677959168|dead-url=no}}</ref>、《[[Vox|Vox]]》<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vox.com/2015/1/7/7507883/charlie-hebdo-explained-covers|title=Charlie Hebdo and its biting satire, explained in 9 of its most iconic covers|author=Amanda Taub|date=2015-01-07|publisher=Vox|access-date=2015-01-10|archive-date=2015-11-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151114173538/http://www.vox.com/2015/1/7/7507883/charlie-hebdo-explained-covers|dead-url=no}}</ref>和《[[自由灯塔|自由灯塔]]》<ref>{{cite web|url=http://freebeacon.com/national-security/a-tribute-to-charlie-hebdo/|title=A Tribute to Charlie Hebdo|publisher=Washington Free Beacon|author=Lachlan Markey|date=2015-01-07|access-date=2015-01-10|archive-date=2015-09-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150910044755/http://freebeacon.com/national-security/a-tribute-to-charlie-hebdo/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。其他新闻机构也报道了枪击事件，但不发布争议画作，如《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》、《[[纽约每日新闻|纽约每日新闻]]》<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/world/1-killed-3-injured-shooting-french-satirical-paper-article-1.2068486|title=Two suspected terrorists located, seven arrests made after three masked gunmen slaughter 12 in Paris at satirical magazine Charlie Hebdo: report|work=Daily News|location=New York|date=2015-01-07|author=Virginia Power, Larry McShane|access-date=2015-01-10|archive-date=2019-05-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190514082826/https://www.nydailynews.com/news/world/1-killed-3-injured-shooting-french-satirical-paper-article-1.2068486|dead-url=no}} ''(cover image pixelated)''</ref>、[[CNN|CNN]]、[[美国半岛电视台|美国半岛电视台]]、[[美联社|美联社]]和《[[每日电讯报|每日电讯报]]》<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/france/11329976/Paris-Charlie-Hebdo-attack-live.html|title=Paris Charlie Hebdo attack: live|work=The Telegraph|date=2015-01-07|author=Andrew Marszal, Barney Henderson and David Millward|access-date=2015-01-10|archive-date=2015-01-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150109194558/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/france/11329976/Paris-Charlie-Hebdo-attack-live.html|dead-url=no}} (as reported by ''Slate'')</ref>。后者被指责[[自我审查|自我审查]]<ref>Hadas Gold (7 January 2015) [http://www.politico.com/blogs/media/2015/01/news-orgs-censor-charlie-hebdo-cartoons-after-attack-200709.html News orgs censor Charlie Hebdo cartoons after attack] {{Wayback|url=http://www.politico.com/blogs/media/2015/01/news-orgs-censor-charlie-hebdo-cartoons-after-attack-200709.html |date=20150321003042 }} [[Politico|Politico]].</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.slate.com/blogs/the_slatest/2015/01/07/charlie_hebdo_cartoons_self_censorship_by_several_major_outlets.html|title=News Outlets Are Censoring Images of Cartoons That May Have Incited Charlie Hebdo Attack|work=Slate|author=Ben Mathis-Lilley|access-date=2015-01-10|archive-date=2015-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151119051616/http://www.slate.com/blogs/the_slatest/2015/01/07/charlie_hebdo_cartoons_self_censorship_by_several_major_outlets.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。此前有反对所有描绘穆罕默德指引的BBC，也公布了《查理周刊》的封面，并声称正审查有关指引<ref>{{cite news|last1=Plunkett|first1=John|title=BBC revises Muhammad ban as BBC1 news bulletin features Charlie Hebdo cover|url=http://www.theguardian.com/media/2015/jan/09/bbc-revises-muhammad-ban-bbc1-news-bulletin-features-charlie-hebdo-cover?CMP=share_btn_tw|accessdate=2015-01-10|work=The Guardian|date=2015-01-09|archive-date=2021-02-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210202005550/https://www.theguardian.com/media/2015/jan/09/bbc-revises-muhammad-ban-bbc1-news-bulletin-features-charlie-hebdo-cover?CMP=share_btn_tw|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

其他媒体，如柏林《[[信使报|信使报]]》和波兰《[[选举报|选举报]]》，在案发翌日转载了《查理周刊》的漫画<ref>[http://pic.twitter.com/AnNQ0PmA29 BERLINER KURIER on Twitter: "Unsere Titelseite von morgen. #JeSuisCharlie http://t.co/4z7CF1RALY"<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>。至少有三家丹麦报社刊登了《查理周刊》的漫画，小报《[[B.T.|B.T.]]》刊登了一幅将穆罕默德悲叹喜欢“白痴”的封面<ref name="rydermadi" />。

埃及日报《Al-Masry Al-Youm》刊登署名为“Je suis Charlie”的年轻漫画家的作品，声援受害者<ref>{{cite web | url=http://english.ahram.org.eg/NewsContent/1/64/119789/Egypt/Politics-/Egypts-cartoonists-pen-their-condemnation-against-.aspx | title=Egypt's cartoonists pen their condemnation against Charlie Hebdo attack | work=Al-Ahram | date=2014-01-08 | accessdate=2015-01-08 | author=Gehad, Reem | archive-date=2015-08-03 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150803193322/http://english.ahram.org.eg/NewsContent/1/64/119789/Egypt/Politics-/Egypts-cartoonists-pen-their-condemnation-against-.aspx | dead-url=no }}</ref>。该报网站也以幻灯片形式摆出《查理周刊》的争议性漫画，这让博主[[乔纳森·盖尔|乔纳森·盖尔]]感到惊讶，也许是“史无前例”的举动，受到当地描绘宗教人物阿拉伯艺术家的施压<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.pri.org/stories/2015-01-07/cartoonists-speak-out-after-slayings-colleagues-paris | title=Cartoonists speak out after slayings of colleagues in Paris | publisher=[[Public_Radio_International|PRI]] | date=2014-01-07 | accessdate=2015-01-08 | archive-date=2020-11-08 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108213653/https://www.pri.org/stories/2015-01-07/cartoonists-speak-out-after-slayings-colleagues-paris | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

媒體大亨[[鲁伯特·默多克|默多克]]於1月10日在推特上發文表示：「也許大多數穆斯林是和平的，但是直到他們承認並摧毀他們不斷壯大的聖戰分子癌瘤前，他們必需為此負責。」他的發言引起爭議。他發表上述推文後，在另一推文表示「政治正確朝向否認和偽善」。<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/charlie-hebdo-attacks-rupert-murdoch-claims-muslims-must-recognise-and-destroy-growing-jihadist-cancer-or-be-held-responsible-9969714.html |title=Rupert Murdoch claims Muslims must 'recognise and destroy growing jihadist cancer' or 'be held responsible' |publisher=The Independent |date=2015-01-10 |quote=Maybe most Moslems peaceful, but until they recognize and destroy their growing jihadist cancer they must be held responsible. |accessdate=2015-01-12 |archive-date=2020-12-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201219000830/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/charlie-hebdo-attacks-rupert-murdoch-claims-muslims-must-recognise-and-destroy-growing-jihadist-cancer-or-be-held-responsible-9969714.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

居住美國的知名華人作家[[陳破空|陳破空]]發表評論：“[[西方國家|西方國家]]的[[民主|民主]]、[[自由|自由]]、[[多元化|多元化]]，被激進的穆斯林所利用，一方面，他們得以在西方國家大明其白地宣傳他們的教義、無所限制的發展他們的宗教，但另一方面，在伊斯蘭國家，除伊斯蘭教之外，其他宗教如[[基督教|基督教]]、[[佛教|佛教]]，卻受到嚴厲的限制和排斥，異教徒受到公開迫害。這種不對等、不對稱的文明博弈，可能導致伊斯蘭教一教獨大，其發展趨勢令人擔憂。”<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://m.voachinese.com/a/voaweishi-20150116-pro-and-con-2/2600964.html |title=焦点对话: 恐袭引争议，欧洲穆斯林化？ |access-date=2015-05-30 |archive-date=2016-03-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304223541/http://m.voachinese.com/a/voaweishi-20150116-pro-and-con-2/2600964.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

===社群行動===
{{seealso|我是查理}}

案發後當晚，數以萬計來自[[法國|法國]]各地聲援的市民及群眾，紛紛聚集於[[查理周刊|查理周刊]]總部附近的[[共和國廣場_(巴黎)|共和國廣場]]悼念亡者。法國各城鎮乃至世界各地，均有民眾發起哀悼儀式<ref name=udn>{{cite news|title=「我是查理」 全歐舉牌挺|url=http://udn.com/news/story/7533/629492|accessdate=2015-01-08|4=|newspaper=台灣聯合報|date=2015年1月8日|archive-date=2019-11-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191129072347/https://udn.com/news/story/7533/629492|dead-url=no}}</ref>。人們以手持「我是查理」（Je suis Charlie）、「無畏」（Not afraid）等標語，或握著象徵[[創意|創意]]的[[鉛筆|鉛筆]]，向罹難的[[漫畫|漫畫]]創作家致哀。同時，網路社群亦出現大量以捍衛[[言論自由|言論自由]]精神為題材的插畫、漫畫作品，如以「[[查理布朗|查理布朗]]也哭了」為題<ref>{{cite news|title=Cartoonists Tweet Responses To Charlie Hebdo Attack|url=http://www.thepoke.co.uk/2015/01/07/cartoonists-tweet-responses-to-charlie-hebdo-attack/#.VK16m2cZ3fY.twitter|accessdate=2015-01-08|newspaper=The Poke|date=2015-01-08|language=en|archive-date=2019-11-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191129115356/https://www.thepoke.co.uk/2015/01/07/cartoonists-tweet-responses-to-charlie-hebdo-attack/#.VK16m2cZ3fY.twitter|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=施旖婕|title=法《查理周刊》遭恐襲　查理布朗哭哭了|url=http://www.nextmag.com.tw/breaking-news/news/20150108/12883213|accessdate=2015-01-08|newspaper=台灣壹周刊|date=2015-01-08|archive-date=2016-03-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160331075342/http://www.nextmag.com.tw/breaking-news/news/20150108/12883213|dead-url=no}}</ref>，以聲援或諷刺恐怖攻擊事件<ref name=newtalk01>{{cite news|title=「我是查理」 數萬民眾上街捍言論自由|url=http://newtalk.tw/news/2015/01/08/55611.html|accessdate=2015-01-08|newspaper=新頭殼newtalk，周佑政/綜合報導|date=2015年1月8日|archive-date=2015-01-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150108185701/http://newtalk.tw/news/2015/01/08/55611.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=storm01>{{cite news|title=巴黎恐怖攻擊 即時報導|url=http://www.stormmediagroup.com/opencms/news/detail/2e79e0d1-9665-11e4-ad2b-ef2804cba5a1/?uuid=2e79e0d1-9665-11e4-ad2b-ef2804cba5a1|accessdate=2015-01-07|4=|newspaper=風傳媒，閻紀宇/綜合報導|date=2015年1月7日|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150108214122/http://www.stormmediagroup.com/opencms/news/detail/2e79e0d1-9665-11e4-ad2b-ef2804cba5a1/?uuid=2e79e0d1-9665-11e4-ad2b-ef2804cba5a1|archive-date=2015-01-08|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=周佩萱|title=漫畫家挺《查理周刊》嘲諷作品沒在怕|url=http://www.appledaily.com.tw/realtimenews/article/international/20150108/538097/%E6%BC%AB%E7%95%AB%E5%AE%B6%E6%8C%BA%E3%80%8A%E6%9F%A5%E7%90%86%E5%91%A8%E5%88%8A%E3%80%8B%E3%80%80%E5%98%B2%E8%AB%B7%E4%BD%9C%E5%93%81%E6%B2%92%E5%9C%A8%E6%80%95|accessdate=2015-01-08|newspaper=台灣蘋果日報|date=2015-01-08|archive-date=2016-03-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305015827/http://www.appledaily.com.tw/realtimenews/article/international/20150108/538097/%E6%BC%AB%E7%95%AB%E5%AE%B6%E6%8C%BA%E3%80%8A%E6%9F%A5%E7%90%86%E5%91%A8%E5%88%8A%E3%80%8B%E3%80%80%E5%98%B2%E8%AB%B7%E4%BD%9C%E5%93%81%E6%B2%92%E5%9C%A8%E6%80%95|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

===屠殺事件支持者===
1月9日在阿富汗[[乌鲁兹甘省|乌鲁兹甘省]]有數百人遊行，讚揚查理周刊總部槍擊案的兇徒。<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/wires/afp/article-2904646/Afghan-demonstration-praises-Charlie-Hebdo-attackers.html |title=Afghan demonstration praises Charlie Hebdo attackers |work=Daily Mail Online |date=2015-01-10 |accessdate=2015-01-12 |archive-date=2015-07-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150713052138/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/wires/afp/article-2904646/Afghan-demonstration-praises-Charlie-Hebdo-attackers.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

1月11日， [[英國|英國]]伊斯蘭教士米扎努爾·拉赫曼（Mizanur Rahman）對槍擊事件表示贊同，又指「英國是伊斯蘭的敵人」<ref>[http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2905075/Hate-preacher-backs-massacres-says-Britain-enemy-Islam.html 'What do you expect if you insult Islam?' British hate preacher BACKS the Paris massacres and tells his followers 'Britain is the enemy of Islam'] {{Wayback|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2905075/Hate-preacher-backs-massacres-says-Britain-enemy-Islam.html |date=20210224085145 }}DailyMail. 2015-01-11</ref>。

以穆罕默德為封面的新一期《查理周刊》出版後，1月15日在巴基斯坦的[[拉合爾|拉合爾]]有約300人遊行，要求絞死該周刊的漫畫家，有示威者的標語稱「製作褻瀆先知的漫畫是最惡劣的恐怖主義行為」。[[博科聖地|博科聖地]]首領[[阿布巴卡爾·謝考|阿布巴卡爾·謝考]]在網上視頻表示為巴黎的屠殺案歡呼。<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2911717/Hang-cartoonists-Pakistani-Muslims-demand-death-sentence-Charlie-Hebdo-staff.html |title=Pakistani Muslims demand death sentence for Charlie Hebdo staff |work=Daily Mail Online |date=2015-01-15 |accessdate=2015-01-16 |archive-date=2020-12-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201225201600/https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2911717/Hang-cartoonists-Pakistani-Muslims-demand-death-sentence-Charlie-Hebdo-staff.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

